And dont even get me started on our disciplines!<br>
Am I so wrong? Are paladins really useful and helpful in groups, am I just exaggerating?  Please show your input, I'd be more than happy to see it.<br>
<br>
All I'm saying is give us paladins something that would make a group want to have us, like crits on undead all the time instead of just with a disc (and this would mean more undead dungeons) or a paladin snare or something useful.<br>
<br>
Feirurr Lupin<br>
55th Knight (LFG) <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/ufeirurrlupin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Feirurr Lupin</A> at: 8/9/01 11:23:19 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#112512><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/uheraklesmoltenbrau.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Herakles Moltenbrau</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Newbie</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#CCCCC8>(8/9/01 12:50:09 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Poor sad, nerfed Paladins</span><hr size=1> I usually don't have much of a problem finding a group when there are people in them that I have fought with before.  That's mainly because I've shown them that I know how to play my paladin well.  I do run into groups that have the misconception that paladins cannot tank in exp groups.  As a paladin, I can:<br>
Stop runners with stun until a root or snare can be placed.<br>
If no snarers are in the group, I can stop fleeing mobs.  Stuns and root make for no runners getting very far.<br>
We have 3 stuns at high lvl that can be chain cast.<br>
Stun to interrupt casting, add bash and you get 4 options, usually 2 or 3 can be used before a spell gets off.<br>
Be the main tank in an exp group.  You'll never be in fear of dying unless your healer is OOM, and then you have LoH as a backup, and Divine Aura.<br>
My damage output with Fiery Defender is pretty high for exp groups.<br>
Taunt anyone who has aggro, except for maybe an overzealous caster who's been chain nuking.<br>
<br>
The key to a paladin is playing it to it's full ability.  Simply hitting auto attack and whacking away at the mob is not playing to full ability.  Use those stuns.  In an intentional taunt fest with another tank, the only one I can't taunt off of at will is a Shadowknight.<br>
<br>
You just need to be able to prove that you are capable of playing your class well, and people will recognize it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#112512><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/bdruzzilro86846.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=urgas>Urgas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Newbie</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#CCCCC8>(8/9/01 1:04:46 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Poor sad, nerfed Paladins</span><hr size=1> Well i am the least to say the paladin class is balanced, but in  a normal exp group pallys just own.<br>
