 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#112512><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/unumenorean.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Numenorean</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_ball.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Druzzil Ro Member</span><br>  Posts: 197<br> <font color=#CCCCC8>(8/11/01 11:24:40 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://w3.one.net/~derek/201.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Paladin Problem...</span><hr size=1> Why an epic ranger? I mean a ranger wielding lets say a lupine dagger and a dragon horn yak or WS, or lam combo will be dealing as much damage as your warrior, plus if he wants to toss out an additional DD or two per fight he will be outdamaging the warrior....not to mention snaring, damage shielding, call of earth and strength of nature buffing, possible chloroplasting (if hes 55th+), and topping off heals, etc...I understand the damage output increase that our epics brings to the table, but honestly a 53+ ranger without epics is still a capable addition. I think it really all boils down to how well you play your class.<br>
<br>
